---
title: "AuctionBidder.bid (Payment Abstraction V2)"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> q_check_access: whenNotPaused, onlyRole(AUCTION_BIDDER_ROLE)
    q_check_access --> q_load: auction = s_auction, assetOut = auction.getAssetOut()

    q_load --> q_check_solution: check solution.length
    q_check_solution --> q_with_callback: solution.length > 0
    q_check_solution --> q_no_callback: solution.length == 0

    q_with_callback --> q_encode_data: data = abi.encode(solution)
    q_no_callback --> q_pre_approve: data = empty, forceApprove(auction, getAssetOutAmount)

    q_encode_data --> q_call_bid: auction.bid(assetIn, amount, data)
    q_pre_approve --> q_call_bid: auction.bid(assetIn, amount, empty)

    q_call_bid --> q_check_residual: bid executed (asset received, callback invoked if data)
    q_check_residual --> q_check_receiver: assetOutBalance = balanceOf(this)

    q_check_receiver --> q_transfer_residual: assetOutBalance > 0 AND receiver != address(0)
    q_check_receiver --> [*]: assetOutBalance == 0 OR receiver == address(0)
    q_transfer_residual --> [*]: safeTransfer(receiver, assetOutBalance)

    note right of q_call_bid
        INV-001: When solution is provided, callback pattern is used (asset swap during callback)
        INV-002: When no solution, pre-approves exact assetOutAmount before bid
        INV-003: Residual assetOut (positive slippage) forwarded to configured receiver
        INV-004: Only AUCTION_BIDDER_ROLE can trigger bid (trusted role via WorkflowRouter)
    end note
